com.example.shoutout.activity.fragment

Class UserSettingsFragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • androidx.fragment.app.Fragment
      • com.example.shoutout.activity.fragment.UserSettingsFragment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, androidx.lifecycle.LifecycleOwner, androidx.lifecycle.ViewModelStoreOwner, androidx.savedstate.SavedStateRegistryOwner

    public class UserSettingsFragment
extends androidx.fragment.app.Fragment
    Fragment that allows the end user to update several properties of their user on the database server. The properties you can change are of the following:
    • Avatar
    • Display name
    • Birthday
    • Biography
    Since:
    April 29, 2021

      • checkEnableSaveButton

        private void checkEnableSaveButton()
        Checks to see if the save button should be enabled, and thus allow the user to submit changes. This is only disabled if the properties stored in the local user are the same as the values in the corresponding fields in this fragment.
